        <p class="bento-desc">BrightLocal gives you geo-grid Maps tracking, citation health across 80+ directories, GBP scoring, and review monitoring. The most complete diagnostic tool under $100/month for local businesses.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See full review <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHODOLOGY -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">How we tested</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">One strict rule: <span class="accent">every tool under $100/month.</span></h2>
      <p>Local SEO agencies charge $1,000–$5,000/month. Most local businesses — dentists, plumbers, HVAC companies, lawyers — cannot justify that cost for rankings they may not see for 6 months. These 10 tools deliver real local SEO results at small business prices. We applied the same 5-criteria scorecard to every tool, with a specific focus on price-to-value ratio.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we measured</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">5 criteria. Price-to-value weighted heavily.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Under $100/month means every dollar counts.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>GBP Management</h4>
              <p>Can it create, schedule, or optimize Google Business Profile content? GBP activity directly impacts local pack rankings — more posts mean more visibility.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content Creation</h4>
              <p>Does it produce blog articles, GBP posts, or social content? Content creation moves rankings. Tracking only measures them. Under $100/month, tools that create are more valuable than tools that report.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Rank Tracking</h4>
              <p>Does it track local keyword rankings or Maps visibility? Geo-grid tracking earns extra credit — single-position averages are too coarse for actionable decisions.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Citation Management</h4>
              <p>Does it build, audit, or distribute business listings? Consistent NAP across directories supports local authority and Maps pack eligibility.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Price-to-Value Ratio</h4>
              <p>What do you actually get per dollar spent? Under $100/month means every dollar must justify itself against the alternative: DIY or no-action.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">What we found</span>
