          <h3 class="ba-title">theStacc Local SEO — Best GBP Automation Under $100</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">For local businesses that need 30 GBP posts per month created and published automatically — at $1.63 per post.</p>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 20px;">theStacc Local SEO creates and publishes 30 Google Business Profile posts per month for $49/month. Topics are researched around your business, industry, location, and the keywords local customers search. No templates to fill, no posts to write, no scheduling to manage. At $49/month, it's the lowest cost-per-post GBP automation on the market. Pair with the Blog SEO module and the 15% bundle discount brings both to ~$126/month — 60 pieces of local content per month combined.</p>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>30 GBP posts per month at $1.63 per post — the cheapest automated GBP content available</h4>
              <p>The next option — paying a VA to write posts — costs $10–$30 per post minimum. theStacc creates posts tailored to your business, industry, and local keywords for $1.63 each.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Content targets local queries — "[service] in [city]" and "near me" keywords</h4>
              <p>Posts aren't generic. Each one targets the specific local search queries your customers use. Service types, neighborhoods, and city names all incorporated into post content.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✓</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Brand voice matching — content sounds like your business</h4>
              <p>After brand voice training during onboarding, posts reflect your tone and terminology — not generic marketing copy. Content passes the "we wrote this" test.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">✗</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Honest con: no rank tracking, review management, or citation building</h4>
              <p>theStacc Local SEO handles GBP content. For tracking, add BrightLocal ($39/mo). For citations, add Moz Local ($20/mo). The three-tool stack costs $108/month and covers the full local SEO foundation.</p>
            </div>
